Cities and buildings of Tomorrow

This is what the future’s sustainable cities could look like

   [gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==]
   De www.nationalgeographic.com - mer, 28/08/2019 - 10:38

     A next-generation metropolis will need to serve people and nature,
     while letting ecology guide its development.

How to Build Sustainable Megacities of the Future?

   [gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==]
   De interestingengineering.com - mar, 07/05/2019 - 16:46

     By 2050, 66% of the world’s population will live in cities. With
     such figures, it is imperative for the city planners to consider
     sustainability as a critical parameter while planning the amenities
     of a megacity. Here are some of the simple yet innovative solutions
     that can help keep megacities sustainable.

Cities of the future: How developers are working to reverse the health and
climate impacts of urban sprawl

   De abcnews.go.com - ven, 15/03/2019 - 13:58

     A National Geographic special issue looks at the way we've built
     cities in the past and how we will reverse the effects on the
     climate and our own health in the future.

How India is building a sustainable city

   [gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==]
   De edition.cnn.com - lun, 29/10/2018 - 10:00

     Amaravati, a new town in Andhra Pradesh, India, is transforming from
     farmland to urban utopia, with British architect Norman Foster's
     firm at the helm. Will it succeed?

